M||tx|---
M||titl|Avoid Layout Thrashing
M||impa|md
M||impa|prevents forced synchronous layouts and reduces perf bottlenecks
M||tags|javascript, dom, css, perf, reflow, layout-thrashing
M||tx|---
M|Avoi|tx|Avoid interleaving style writes w/ layout reads. When you read a layout property (like `offsetWidth`, `getBoundingClientRect()`, or `getComputedStyle()`) btw style changes, the browser is forced to trigger a synchronous reflow.
M|Avoi|**Th|**
M|Avoi|tx|```ts
M|Avoi|func|HTMLElement) {
M|Avoi|tx|// Each line invalidates style, but browser batches the recalculation
M|Avoi|tx|element.style.width = '100px'
M|Avoi|tx|element.style.height = '200px'
M|Avoi|tx|element.style.backgroundColor = 'blue'
M|Avoi|tx|element.style.border = '1px solid black'
M|Avoi|tx|}
M|Avoi|tx|```
M|Avoi|**In|**
M|Avoi|tx|```ts
M|Avoi|func|HTMLElement) {
M|Avoi|tx|element.style.width = '100px'
M|Avoi|tx|const width = element.offsetWidth  // Forces reflow
M|Avoi|tx|element.style.height = '200px'
M|Avoi|tx|const height = element.offsetHeight  // Forces another reflow
M|Avoi|tx|}
M|Avoi|tx|```
M|Avoi|**Co|**
M|Avoi|tx|```ts
M|Avoi|func|HTMLElement) {
M|Avoi|tx|// Batch all writes together
M|Avoi|tx|element.style.width = '100px'
M|Avoi|tx|element.style.height = '200px'
M|Avoi|tx|element.style.backgroundColor = 'blue'
M|Avoi|tx|element.style.border = '1px solid black'
M|Avoi|tx|// Read after all writes are done (single reflow)
M|Avoi|tx|const { width, height } = element.getBoundingClientRect()
M|Avoi|tx|}
M|Avoi|tx|```
M|Avoi|**Co|**
M|Avoi|tx|```ts
M|Avoi|func|HTMLElement) {
M|Avoi|tx|// Read phase - all layout queries first
M|Avoi|tx|const rect1 = element.getBoundingClientRect()
M|Avoi|tx|const offsetWidth = element.offsetWidth
M|Avoi|tx|const offsetHeight = element.offsetHeight
M|Avoi|tx|// Write phase - all style changes after
M|Avoi|tx|element.style.width = '100px'
M|Avoi|tx|element.style.height = '200px'
M|Avoi|tx|}
M|Avoi|tx|```
M|Avoi|**Be|use CSS classes**
M|Avoi|tx|```css
M|Avoi|tx|.highlighted-box {
M|Avoi|widt|100px;
M|Avoi|heig|200px;
M|Avoi|back|blue;
M|Avoi|bord|1px solid black;
M|Avoi|tx|}
M|Avoi|tx|```
M|Avoi|tx|```ts
M|Avoi|func|HTMLElement) {
M|Avoi|tx|element.classList.add('highlighted-box')
M|Avoi|tx|const { width, height } = element.getBoundingClientRect()
M|Avoi|tx|}
M|Avoi|tx|```
M|Avoi|**Re|**
M|Avoi|tx|```tsx
M|Avoi|// I|interleaving style changes w/ layout queries
M|Avoi|func|{ isHighlighted: boolean }) {
M|Avoi|tx|const ref = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null)
M|Avoi|tx|useEffect(() => {
M|Avoi|tx|if (ref.current && isHighlighted) {
M|Avoi|tx|ref.current.style.width = '100px'
M|Avoi|tx|const width = ref.current.offsetWidth // Forces layout
M|Avoi|tx|ref.current.style.height = '200px'
M|Avoi|tx|}
M|Avoi|tx|}, [isHighlighted])
M|Avoi|tx|return <div ref={ref}>cn</div>
M|Avoi|tx|}
M|Avoi|// C|toggle class
M|Avoi|func|{ isHighlighted: boolean }) {
M|Avoi|tx|return (
M|Avoi|<div|''}>
M|Avoi|tx|cn
M|Avoi|tx|</div>
M|Avoi|tx|)
M|Avoi|tx|}
M|Avoi|tx|```
M|Avoi|tx|Prefer CSS classes over inline styles when possible. CSS files are cached by the browser, and classes provide better separation of concerns and are easier to maintain.
M|Avoi|See |//gist.github.com/paulirish/5d52fb081b3570c81e3a) and [CSS Triggers](https://csstriggers.com/) for more information on layout-forcing operations.